Nimble Storage is a predictive flash storage technology company based in San Jose, California founded in early 2008. It produces hardware and software products for data storage, specifically data storage arrays that use the iSCSI and Fibre Channel protocols and includes data backup and data protection features.[1] Nimble is a subsidiary of Hewlett Packard Enterprise. [2]




Dawn at Nimble Storage's campus in San Jose, California





