Dr. Naveen Bewtra


Dr. Naveen Bewtra currently heads his own consulting firm, Bewtra and Associates, where he works with early stage startups providing Strategic Advice across a wide spectrum of industry verticals. 

Read more about Dr. Naveen Bewtra
 





Gopal Sundaramoorthy


Gopal is the President, Cetas Healthcare Americas and Head, Strategy Consulting and Founder & CEO of Grow Beyond, LLC. Gopal's career spans world class diagnostic imaging companies and academic institutions. This proven, progressive leadership experience is deeply rooted in his multi-country/multi-cultural upbringing, and his unshakable passion to use high-technology into creating affordable, distinctive, innovative and meaningful healthcare solutions. 

Read more about Gopal Sundaramoorthy
 





Rick Bullotta


Rick Bullotta is a Managing Partner at NextBigThing, a strategic advisory and investing firm, where he works closely with startup innovators. Rick was the Co-Founder and CTO of ThingWorx, provider of an innovative application software platform for the Internet of Things. ThingWorx was acquired by PTC in 2013. Rick was also the Co-Founder and CTO of Lighthammer Software Development (acquired by SAP in 2005), where he was responsible for the conceptualization and development of innovative web-based and service-enabled software products targeted at the manufacturing industry. 

Read more about Rick Bullotta
 





Steve Rubin


Steve has 25 years of a proven track record as a successful senior-level executive, board of directors member and advisory board member. He maximizes corporate performance and enhances board directives for startups. He has been with six startups: one is now listed on a public exchange; three others have been acquired by Wells Fargo, Francisco Partners and Microsoft. He understands the startup culture and expectations. He currently sits on three advisory boards and two boards of directors. 

Read more about Steve Rubin
 





Siki Giunta


Siki is a well-recognized leader in the IoT and M2M space. Prior to joining Glassbeam, she was the global senior vice president of cloud and connected solutions for Verizon Enterprise Solutions. In this role, Siki was responsible for Verizon’s end-to-end global cloud ecosystem, as well as technology convergence and connected solutions through the company’s wireline and wireless networks. 

Read more about Siki Giunta
 





Eric Milledge


Eric is the Chairman of Symetis S.A. where he assists with an innovative and minimally invasive heart valve replacement device which uses transapical and transfemoral delivery systems. Prior to this, he spent 37 years in the pharmaceuticals and medical devices industry with Johnson & Johnson and private medical device startup companies. He spent eight years as the President of Johnson & Johnson and nine years as the Group Chairman. 

Read more about Eric Milledge
 





Vic Mahadevan


Vic is an enterprise consultant and currently sits on the boards of many enterprise startups. Recently, he was appointed to the Board of Directors at Violin Memory. Previously, Vic was the CSO of NetApp and the VP of Marketing at LSI Corp where he drove all aspects of Product Management, Outbound Marketing, and Business Alliances. Since November 2012, Vic has also been sitting on the board of directors of Overland Storage, Inc., a provider of data management and data protection products.
 

Read more about Vic Mahadevan
 



 









